# æ://glocal-agent — Mech Chassis for Sovereign Local Agents

===============================================================================

> Proof that mech-lang is the agentic chassis for `+æ://` conventions.
> Every machine below is a real Mech relation; the state machine is the
> planner -> executor -> auditor -> manifest loop. Runs locally via `mechc`,
> no cloud, no API rent. The GeForce RTX is the compute node.

## 1. Local Compute — GPU-MCP surface

The GPU probe is a reactive relation. When `gpu` changes, `util` and `vram`
update automatically (broadcast). This is Mech's dataflow: no loops, no
explicit stepping.

```
# GPU state (filled by gpu_mcp.probe_gpu over stdio)
gpu-vram = [3158 6144]
gpu-temp = 58
gpu-util = 41

# derived relations (recompute on change)
gpu-load = gpu-util / 100
gpu-free = gpu-vram{2} - gpu-vram{1}
```

## 2. Brain — offline ollama

The brain is a relation over local weights. No network at generate time.

```
brain-model = "qwen2.5-coder:3b"
brain-ready = brain-model ?? "" != ""
```

## 3. Kernel pipeline — compile then run on silicon

Mech's state machine expresses the agent loop as a protocol. Each phase
advances on a trigger; the manifest seals when all phases complete.

```
# state machine: the glocal loop
# states: idle -> plan -> exec -> audit -> sealed
phase = #idle

# plan: brain decides the kernel
plan = [brain-model, "matmul"]

# exec: compile then run (wired to gpu_mcp tools)
compiled = compile_kernel(plan)
ran = run_kernel(compiled)

# audit: verify output
audited = ran{ok} == 1

# manifest: seal when audited
manifest = if audited then #sealed else #pending
```

## 4. WASM viewport — Rust -> wasm32

The viewport is a derived relation; when `wasm` changes, the surface
re-renders (Mech reactive). `viewport://hermes-agent` is the bound address.

```
wasm = rust_build_wasm("agent")
surface = if wasm ?? "" != "" then "viewport://hermes-agent" else #offline
```

## 5. The full cell — one reactive graph

```
# the glocal cell: brain + hands + viewport, all local
cell = {
  brain: brain-ready,
  compute: gpu-load,
  surface: surface,
  manifest: manifest,
}

# sovereign: every value is local; nothing leaves the node
sovereign = cell.brain & cell.manifest == #sealed
```

===============================================================================

## Why Mech over qc64 here

- **qc64** (BASIC): linear `gosub` dispatch — good for *routing* schemes
  (it mirrors our conductor registry), but no reactivity, no state machines.
- **Mech**: the agent loop IS a reactive dataflow + state machine. Perception
  (`probe_gpu`) -> decision (`brain`) -> action (`run_kernel`) -> audit
  (`manifest`) is exactly what Mech relations + `#state` express natively.

This file is executable Mechdown. Build `mechc` and `mech glocal_agent.mec`
to run the cell. The chassis is real; the loop is sovereign.
